#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:1
msgid "Wrapping Tools"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:3
msgid ""
"The wrapping tools consist of executables that pull information from C++ "
"header files, and produce wrapper code that allows the C++ interfaces to be "
"used from other programming languages (Python and Java).  One can think of "
"the wrappers as having a front-end that parses C++ header files, and a back-"
"end that produces language-specific glue code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:9
msgid ""
"All of the code in this directory is C, rather than C++.  One might think "
"this is silly, since the front-end parses C++ .h files and the back-end "
"generates .cxx files.  The original reason for this is that the parser uses "
"lex and yacc, which are written in C and previously could not easily be "
"linked into C++ programs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:16
msgid "The C++ Parser"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:18
msgid "vtkParse"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:20
msgid ""
"The header vtkParse.h provides a C API for the C++ parser that wrappers use "
"to read the VTK header files.  The parser consists of three critical pieces: "
"a preprocessor (see below), a lex-based lexical analyzer (lex.yy.c, "
"generated from vtkParse.l) and a bison-based glr parser (vtkParse.tab.c, "
"generated from vtkParse.y).  Instructions on rebuilding the parser are "
"provided at the end of this document."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:27
msgid "vtkParsePreprocess"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:29
msgid ""
"This is a preprocessor that can run independently of the parser.  In "
"general, the parser does not recursively parse `#include` files, but it does "
"recursively preprocess them in order to gather all of the macro definitions "
"within them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:34
msgid "vtkParseString"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:36
msgid ""
"This provides low-level string handling routines that are used by the parser "
"and the preprocessor.  Most importantly, it contains a C++ tokenizer.  It "
"also contains a cache for storing strings (type names, etc.) that are "
"encountered during the parse."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:41
msgid "vtkParseSystem"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:43
msgid ""
"This contains utilities for file system access.  One of its functionalities "
"is to manage a cache of where header files are located on the file system, "
"so that header file lookups can be done inexpensively even on slow file "
"systems."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:47
msgid "vtkParseType"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:49
msgid ""
"This is a header file that defines numerical constants that we use to "
"identify C++ types, type qualifiers, and specifiers.  These constants are "
"used in the vtkParseData data structures described below."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:53
msgid "vtkParseAttributes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:55
msgid ""
"This is a header file that defines numerical constants for wrapper-specific "
"attributes that can be added to declarations in the VTK header files.  For "
"example, `[[vtk::wrapexclude]]` and ``[[vtk::deprecated]]``.  These "
"attribute constants are stored in the vtkParseData data structures."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:60
msgid "vtkParseData"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:62
msgid ""
"The data structures defined in vtkParseData.h are used for the output of the "
"parser.  This header provides data structures for namespaces, classes, "
"methods, typedefs, and for other entities that can be declared in a C++ "
"file.  The wrappers convert this data into wrapper code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:68
msgid "Parser Utilities"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:70
msgid "vtkParseExtras"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:72
msgid ""
"This file provides routines for managing certain abstractions of the data "
"that is produced by the parser.  Most specifically, it provides facilities "
"for expanding typedefs and for instantiating templates.  Its code is not "
"pretty."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:76
msgid "vtkParseMerge"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:78
msgid ""
"This provides methods for dealing with method resolution order.  It defines "
"a data structure for managing a class along with all the classes it derives "
"from.  It is needed for managing tricky details relating to inheritance, "
"such as \"using\" declarations, overrides, virtual methods, etc."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:83
msgid "vtkParseMangle"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:85
msgid ""
"The Python wrappers rely on name-mangling routines to convert C++ names into "
"names that can be used in Python.  The mangling is done according to the "
"rules of the IA64 ABI (this same mangling is used to convert C++ APIs into C "
"APIs)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:90
msgid "vtkParseHierarchy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:92
msgid ""
"A hierarchy file is a text file that lists information about all the types "
"defined in a VTK module.  The wrappers use these files to look up types from "
"names.  Through the use of vtkParseHierarchy, the wrappers can get detailed "
"information about a type even if the header file only contains a forward "
"reference, as long as the type is defined somewhere in another header."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:98
msgid "vtkParseMain"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:100
msgid ""
"A common main() function for use by wrapper tool executables.  It provides a "
"standard set of command-line options as well as response-file handling.  It "
"also invokes the parser."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:105
msgid "Wrapper Utilities"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:107
msgid "vtkWrap"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:109
msgid ""
"This has functions that are common to the wrapper tools for all the wrapper "
"languages.  Unlikely vtkParse, it deals with the generation of code, rather "
"than the parsing of code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:113
msgid "vtkWrapText"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:115
msgid ""
"This has functions for automatically generating documentation from the "
"header files that are parsed.  It produces the Python docstrings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:119
msgid "Python-Specific Utilities"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:121
msgid "These are named according to the pieces of wrapper code they produce."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:123
msgid "__vtkWrapPythonClass__ creates type objects for vtkObjectBase classes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:124
msgid "__vtkWrapPythonType__ creates type objects for other wrapped classes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:125
msgid "__vtkWrapPythonMethod__ for calling C++ methods from Python"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:126
msgid ""
"__vtkWrapPythonOverload__ maps a Python method to multiple C++ overloads"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:127
msgid ""
"__vtkWrapPythonMethodDef__ generates the method tables for wrapped classes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:128
msgid "__vtkWrapPythonTemplate__ for wrapping of C++ class templates"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:129
msgid "__vtkWrapPythonNamespace__ for wrapping namespaces"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:130
msgid "__vtkWrapPythonEnum__ creates type objects for enum types"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:131
msgid ""
"__vtkWrapPythonConstant__ adds C++ constants to Python classes, namespaces"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:134
msgid "Python Wrapper Executables"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:136
msgid "vtkWrapPython"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:138
msgid ""
"This executable will parse the C++ declarations from a header file and "
"produce wrapper code that can be linked into a Python extension module."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:141
msgid "vtkWrapPythonInit"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:143
msgid ""
"This will produce the PyInit entry point for a Python extension module, as "
"well as code for loading all the dependent modules.  The .cxx file produced "
"by vtkWrapPythonInit is linked together to the .cxx files that are produced "
"by vtkWrapPython to create the module."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:149
msgid "Java Wrapper Executables"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:151
msgid "__vtkWrapJava__ produces C++ wrapper code that uses the JNI"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:152
msgid "__vtkParseJava__ produces Java code that sits on top of the C++ code"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:155
msgid "Other Executables"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:157
msgid "vtkWrapHierarchy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:159
msgid ""
"This will slurp up all the header files in a VTK module and produce a "
"\"hierarchy.txt\" file that provides information about all of the types that "
"are defined in that module.  In other words, it provides a summary of the "
"module's contents.  The Python and Java wrapper executables rely on these "
"\"hierarchy.txt\" files in order to look up types by name."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:166
msgid "vtkWrapSerDes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:168
msgid ""
"This generates C++ code to serialize a VTK object into json and deserialize "
"the object back from json. This relies upon the property parser from "
"`vtkParseProperties`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:172
msgid "Rebuilding the Parser"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:174
msgid ""
"The code for the C++ parser is generated from the files vtkParse.l and "
"vtkParse.y with the classic compiler-generator tools lex and yacc (or, more "
"specifically, with their modern incarnations flex and bison).  These tools "
"are readily available on macOS and Linux systems, and they can be installed "
"(with some difficulty) on Windows systems."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:180
msgid ""
"The C code that flex and bison generate is not styled according to VTK "
"standards, and must be cleaned up in order to compile without warnings and "
"in order to satisfy VTK's git hooks and style checks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:184
msgid "vtkParse.l"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:186
msgid ""
"The file vtkParse.l contains regular expressions for tokenizing a C++ header "
"file.  It is used to generate the file lex.yy.c, which is directly included "
"(i.e. as a C file) by the main parser file, vtkParse.tab.c."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:190
msgid "To generate lex.yy.c from vtkParse.l, use the following steps."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:192
msgid "Get a copy of flex, version 2.6.4 or later"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:193
msgid "Run `flex --nodefault --noline -olex.yy.c vtkParse.l`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:194
msgid "In an editor, remove blank lines from the top and bottom of lex.yy.c"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:195
msgid "Replace all tabs with two spaces (e.g. `:%s/\\t/  /g` in vi)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:196
msgid "Remove spaces from the ends of lines (e.g. `:%s/  *$//` in vi)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:197
msgid "Remove `struct yy_trans_info`, which is used nowhere in the code"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:198
msgid "Add the following code at line 23 (after \"`end standard C headers`\")"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:200
msgid "#ifndef __cplusplus  extern int isatty(int);  #endif /* __cplusplus */"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:204
msgid ""
"Finally, if you have clang-format installed, you can use it to re-style the "
"code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:207
msgid "vtkParse.y"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:209
msgid ""
"The file vtkParse.y contains the rules for parsing a C++ header file. Many "
"of the rules in this file have the same names as in the description of the "
"grammar in the official ISO standard.  The file vtkParse.y is used to "
"generate the file vtkParse.tab.c, which contains the parser."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:214
msgid "Get a copy of bison 3.8.2 or later, it has a yacc-compatible front end."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:215
msgid ""
"Run `bison --no-lines -b vtkParse vtkParse.y`, to generate vtkParse.tab.c"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:216
msgid ""
"In an editor, replace every `static inline` in vtkParse.tab.c with `static`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:217
msgid "Replace `#if ! defined lint || defined __GNUC__` with `#if 1`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:218
msgid "remove `YY_ATTRIBUTE_UNUSED` from `yyfillin`, `yyfill`, and `yynormal`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:219
msgid "comment out the `break;` after `return yyreportAmbiguity`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:220
msgid "replace `(1-yyrhslen)` with `(1-(int)yyrhslen)`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:221
msgid ""
"replace `sizeof yynewStates[0]` and `sizeof yyset->yystates[0]` with "
"`sizeof(yyGLRState*)`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:222
msgid ""
"replace `sizeof yynewLookaheadNeeds[0]` and `sizeof yyset-"
">yylookaheadNeeds[0]` with `sizeof(yybool)`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:223
msgid ""
"replace `sizeof yynewItems[0]` and `sizeof yystackp->yynextFree[0]` with "
"`sizeof(yyGLRStackItem)`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:225
msgid ""
"If you are familiar with \"diff\" and \"patch\" and if you have clang-"
"format, you can automate these code changes as follows.  For this, you must "
"use exactly version 3.8.2 of bison to ensure that the code that is produced "
"is as similar as possible to what is currently in the VTK repository."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:230
msgid "Run bison (as above) on the vtkParse.y from the master branch"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:231
msgid "Use clang-format-14 to re-style vtkParse.tab.c to match VTK code style"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:232
msgid "Use \"git diff -R vtkParse.tab.c\" to produce a patch file"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:234
msgid ""
"If done correctly, this will produce a patch file that contains all the "
"changes above (steps 3 through 9 in the original list).  Load the patch file "
"into a text editor to verify that this is so, and remove any superfluous "
"changes from the patch file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:239
msgid ""
"Then, switch to your new vtkParse.y (the one you have modified).  Repeat "
"steps 1 and 2 (generate vtkParse.tab.c and reformat it with clang-format). "
"Now you can apply the patch file to automate the original steps 3 through 9. "
"Note that as you continue to edit vtkParse.y and regenerate vtkParse.tab.c, "
"you can continue to use the same patch.  Just remember to run clang-format "
"every time that you run bison."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:246
msgid "Debugging the Parser"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:248
msgid ""
"When bison is run, it should not report any shift/reduce or reduce/reduce "
"warnings.  If modifications to the rules cause these warnings to occur, you "
"can run bison with the `--debug` and `--verbose` options:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:252
msgid "bison --debug --verbose -b vtkParse vtkParse.y\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/Tools/README.md:254
msgid ""
"This will cause bison to produce a file called \"vtkParse.output\" that will "
"show which rules conflict with other rules."
msgstr ""
